This code numerically solves the 2D lid-driven cavity flow, a fundamental test case in CFD, with the addition of passive scalar transport. Both the fluid and scalar are simulated in a unit-square domain, discretized on a staggered grid. The lid-driven geometry consists of three stationary walls and a top ŌĆ£lidŌĆØ moving at fixed speed, generating rich vortex structures and secondary flows, which makes it ideal for validating Navier-Stokes solvers.

